      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a great start, i like the phrasing 'economic scaffolding'. for the next section, i want to tackle the counter-arguments. most people who oppose this usually bring up the idea of meritocracy—basically that people should just work hard and get what they deserve. how can i frame that argument as being fundamentally flawed or even outdated in the context of modern systemic racism? i want to make sure the essay shows why meritocracy is a bit of a myth in this specific case.",
