      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The concept of meritocracy is a dangerous illusion when confronted with entrenched systemic racism. It falsely assumes a level playing field, ignoring how historical policies and current institutional biases create vastly different starting lines for different racial groups. When one group inherits generational wealth and access to superior resources, \"hard work\" alone cannot overcome the structural advantages they possess. Therefore, framing outcomes solely on individual effort conveniently masks the deep-seated, racially biased architecture of our economic system.",
      "source": "target",
